title: Abstract Painting Retreat
shortDescription: Abstract Painting Retreat on the Big Island of Hawaii
description: Explore the beauty of the Big Island of Hawaii while you expand your creativity. Be inspired by the ocean, sun, rainbows, breezes, dolphins, whales, and exotic flowers. In this retreat, you will practice new skills & learn techniques to help you feel more confident as an artist. Using gentle and supportive critique, Abbie will help guide you so that you can refine your artistic vision. Whether you are new to intuitive art or an experienced abstract artist, I will find a level of instruction that is comfortable for you. All levels welcome! Includes: 4-hrs/daily prompts & guided instruction, 2 healthy organic meals/day, excursions to geothermal warm ponds, lava cliffs, black sand beaches, tons of aloha! Available locally: yoga, sound healing, massage, EFT, Watsu.

title: French Landscape Painting
shortDescription: French Landscape Painting & Drawing Workshop at Perigord Retreats
description:
Join Nina Weiss this summer in France for the experience of a lifetime!
 Located in the French countryside, Perigord Retreats offers
 us so much! Beautiful landscapes, comfortable, cozy accommodations;
 a fully equipped indoor studio 24/7, lovingly crafted local foods,
 an indoor swimming pool, under-the-stars hot tub; and every-day private 
excursions into the stunning landscapes, markets, and medieval towns
 of the Dordogne and Lot regions. Imagine your art adventure in some 
of the most scenic, unique towns and landscapes of Southern France!
 Now in her twenty-second year of leading European Landscape Workshops,
 Nina is a practicing professional painter and a dedicated, patient
 and experienced teacher. All levels of experience invited! We can't
 wait to share it all with you!!!

title: Kristy Kutch Colored Pencil Workshops
description: Kristy Kutch has been creating colored pencil art for almost thirty years and has been teaching colored pencilworkshops since 1991. A teacher with a life license, she applies many basic learning principles to her workshops, enthusiastically meeting each student at the appropriate level. Beginners are always welcome, but even advanced artists benefit from Kristy's instruction. Offering demonstrations of techniques  and the characteristics of different types of colored pencils, papers,and other related materials, Kristy covers a wide range of possibilities. Kristy is the author of Drawing and Painting with Colored Pencil and The New Colored Pencil. She is also the feature artist in the Artist Palette Productions DVD "Colored Pencil Landscapes: Beyond The Basics". Kristy's workshops are held nationwide; each is an enjoyable, supportive, memorable experience in a beautiful location. Visit www.artshow.com/kutch/ or contact Kristy at kakutch@earthlink.net or 219-874-4688.
